@NODE What " What is Blitz-Twit"

Blitz-Twit is a program to help prevent those annoying users from calling
your BBS.

It allows you to screen out users by phone number or username.

Some features:

       o Strips all non-numerical characters from phone number before
         comparing.
       o Has a test mode which allows the sysop to run the program without
         actually killing the user off.
       o Keeps a log of all users that have been twitted.


@ENDNODE
@NODE setup " Setting up Blitz-Twit"

Blitz-Twit can take several parameters. Call it thus:

       Blitz-Twit [-P] [-T] [-R]

  Where:

       -P            : Do NOT kill the user for a failed phone test.
       -T            : Test mode. Doesn't kill the user.
       -R            : Print a [PRESS RETURN] after the displayed text.

-P is provided in case the person entered a silly phone number for various
reasons. If they can't explain themselves, you could then add their name to
the twit config.

You should put this command in your login.(dlg)batch file early on, or later
on if you want to tease the twits!

@ENDNODE

@NODE config "Config file for Blitz-Twit."

Blitz-Twit requires a config file to run. The config file is called
'DLGConfig:Misc/Blitz-Twit.cfg'. It is a simple text file which has 1 or more
groups of 3 lines. The three lines are:

       Line 1        : P for phone or N for name.
       Line 2        : Text file to display if the user fails this particular
                       test.
       Line 3        : The phone number or name.

You may have as many of these as you wish, and you may use the same text file
for each if you so desire.

@ENDNODE
